            I spent the afternoon and night with work. On the way to the A Space Cebu, I made a small detour to a food market called Lenders. This seems to be a wholesaler. But you come in as a tourist when a passport was presented. It was somehow strange to see that so many people have to buy in large quantities and in abundance and only have to earn their livelihood on the street in which they have to drive individual fruits or chewing gum past or sell at the end of the traffic lights. A life -threatening affair in the driving style. </p>
        <p> Once in the office, everything went well fundamentally, but unfortunately the internet line was not so hit. The internet management worked much better in my accommodation. But I also have it for myself. </p>
        <p> Tonight there was also a meetup in the A Space Cebu, which I wanted to go. A meetup is a meeting of an interest group and these are usually public and free of charge. There are many different ones distributed over the world. I myself often support my colleagues in making maps in organizing a meetup, which are often about IT topics. </p>
