        <p> Today was the first meeting of the WordPress Meetup Group in Cebu. In the beginning everyone should introduce themselves briefly and communicate their IT/WordPress knowledge. I mentioned that my specialty is architecture and testing of web applications. I was promptly asked to take part in a discussion round, since unfortunately a loaded software architect did not appear. The discussion was quite pleasant and, even in some questions, went completely into my specialty testing of availability as well as the topic of clean code and remote working came up. After the Meetup, I talked to several software developers and made it even subliminally advertising for card making as an employer. 3 of their knowledge was even more than interesting for us. Let's see if someone is applying. </p>
